com.magnet.android.mms.utils.logger

Class Log

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.magnet.android.mms.utils.logger.Log

  • public final class Log
extends Object
    Wrapper class for Android logs. This class outputs log information using the existing Log class, prepended with the "MagnetMobile" tag.

      • setLoggable

        public static void setLoggable(int level)

        Parameters:
        level - The global log level.

      • isLoggable

        public static boolean isLoggable(int level)
        Determine whether the global log level is at least at the specified level.
        Parameters:
        level - The global log level.
        Returns:
        true if the global log level is at least at the specified level; false otherwise.

      • setLoggable

        public static boolean setLoggable(String tag,
                  int level)
        Set the log level for the specified tag in this process.
        Parameters:
        tag - The log tag.
        level - The log level: SUPPRESS , VERBOSE , DEBUG , INFO , WARN , ERROR
        Returns:
        true if the log level was successfully set; otherwise an exception is thrown.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Invalid log level.

      • isLoggable

        public static boolean isLoggable(String tag,
                 int level)
        Determine whether the log level for the tag is at least at the specified level. If no level is set for the specified tag, it will compare against sGlobalLogLevel. A log level with SUPPRESS always returns false. Use this method or isLoggable(int) to guard against v(String, String) and d(String, String).
        Parameters:
        tag - The log tag.
        level - The log level: VERBOSE, DEBUG, INFO, WARN, ERROR
        Returns:
        true if the log level for the tag is at least at the specified level; false otherwise.
